var HELP = `learning-with-court CLI

Usage:
  lwc                                Run as stdio MCP proxy (used by agents).
  lwc setup <workshop-id> [--dir <path>]
                                     Install a workshop (default
                                     ~/learning-with-court/<workshop-id>).
  lwc list                           Show installed workshops.
  lwc catalog                        Show available workshops from
                                     workshop.institute (the public catalog).
  lwc switch <workshop-id>           Print 'cd <path>' for the workshop.
                                     (eval \\\`lwc switch <id>\\\` to cd in shell.)
  lwc update [<workshop-id>] [--token-only]
                                     Refresh + git pull. Updates all installed
                                     workshops if no id is given. Preserves
                                     learner edits in src/.
  lwc reset-workshop [--yes]         Discard src/ edits and restore it to
                                     the workshop's pinned pre-state tag.
                                     Run from inside the workshop dir.
  lwc advance --to <slug> [--yes]    Move src/ to a lesson's pre-state tag.
                                     Run from inside the workshop dir.
  lwc state                          Read-only summary of the current
                                     workshop: pinned tag + src/ drift.
  lwc remove <workshop-id> [--delete-files]
                                     Drop from registry; --delete-files also
                                     removes the on-disk clone.
  lwc auth login | logout | status   Manage cached sign-in token.
  lwc env set <NAME>                 Store a secret (e.g. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY).
                                     Prompts hidden; value never echoed.
                                     Stored at ~/.lwc/env.json (chmod 600).
  lwc env get <NAME>                 Print stored value to stdout. Refuses when
                                     stdout is a TTY or an agent context is
                                     detected (CLAUDECODE=1). Safe for shell
                                     interpolation: KEY=$(lwc env get FOO).
                                     Force print: lwc env get FOO | cat.
  lwc env has <NAME>                 Exit 0 if NAME is stored; exit 1 if not.
                                     Prints nothing \u2014 safe for agent walkers.
  lwc env list                       Print names of stored secrets (no values).
  lwc env delete <NAME>              Remove a stored secret.
  lwc env switch <dev|prod>          Persist active platform env target
                                     at ~/.lwc/config.json. Subsequent
                                     lwc invocations route to this env
                                     without setting LWC_API_URL.
  lwc env current                    Print active env + resolved URLs.
  lwc help                           Show this help.

Environment:
  LWC_TOKEN            Bypass cached/browser flow with a Bearer token (CI use).
  LWC_API_URL          Override the platform base URL. Wins over the active
                       env from \`lwc env switch\`. Default is derived from
                       the active env (prod = https://mcp.workshop.institute,
                       dev = https://mcp-dev.workshop.institute).
  LWC_LANDING_URL      Override the landing-site URL. Wins over the active
                       env's landing URL.
`;
